# Testing

- Pytest uses an isolated Postgres DB (`ALS_TEST_DATABASE_URL`, default `postgresql://als:als@localhost:5432/als_intel_test`).
- `tests/conftest.py` creates that DB if missing and truncates **only** it between tests — never wipe `als_intel` (app data).
- Create/migrate with `make init-test-db`.
- Seed data via `EvidenceStore()` or inline JSONL — do not rely on SQLite files.
- Mirror production imports: `from als_intel...`.
- Web UI tests: spin `ThreadingHTTPServer`, call endpoints with `urllib.request` (see `test_webui_api.py`).
- Avoid live network calls; mock or use fixture files under `tests/fixtures/`.
- Update `tests/fixtures/regression_queries.json` only when chat or guardrail behavior changes.
